  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  60 ASA physical status I-III patients, between the ages of 18 and 59 years, scheduled
             for elective thoracotomy surgery with general anaesthesia were included in this study

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  severe hepatorenal disease history, sensitivity or contraindication to morphine and
             remifentanil, chronic pain (defined as regular use of opioid analgesics for &gt; 3
             months), drug or alcohol abuse and contraindication to administration of PCA
      </textblock>
